    },
    {
      "text": "For an SSD, locate the M.2 slot on the motherboard, insert the drive at a 30-degree angle, press it flat, and secure with the small retaining screw. For a SATA drive, slide it into a drive bay and screw it in place.",
      "title": "Install the storage drive"
    },
    {
      "text": "If using a SATA drive, connect one end of a SATA data cable to the drive and the other to a SATA port on the motherboard. Then connect a SATA power cable from the PSU to the drive's power connector.",
      "title": "Connect SATA drive cables"
    },
    {
      "text": "Locate a PCIe x16 slot on the motherboard — the longest slot, closest to the CPU. Remove the corresponding metal bracket(s) from the rear of the case. Press the retention clip at the end of the slot outward to open it.",
      "title": "Prepare the GPU slot"
    },
    {
      "text": "Hold the GPU by its edges and align the gold contacts with the PCIe x16 slot. Press down firmly and evenly until you hear a click and the retention clip snaps back. The GPU bracket should align with the case's rear opening.",
