    {
      "text": "Connect the PCIe power cables from the PSU to the GPU's power connectors — typically 6-pin or 8-pin connectors on the top or rear of the card. If the GPU requires two connectors, plug in both. The fan side should face down.",
      "title": "Connect GPU power cables"
    },
    {
      "text": "Connect the front panel cables to the motherboard headers. These thin cables include Power SW, Reset SW, HDD LED, and Power LED. Check your motherboard manual for the exact pin layout — they're usually in the bottom-right corner.",
