    },
    {
      "text": "Connect the front panel audio header (HD Audio or AC97) to the AAFP header on the motherboard, usually near the bottom-left corner. The connector is keyed — align the missing pin before pressing in.",
      "title": "Connect the audio header"
    },
    {
      "text": "With everything connected, do a visual sweep: check all power connectors are fully seated, RAM clips are locked, all screws are tight, and no loose cables are near fans. Route cables away from airflow paths if possible.",
